Headache; 16 years old received vaccine; A spontaneous report was received from a patient concerning a 16-year-old female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced headache and 16 years old received vaccine. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 21-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first dose of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 23-Jan-2021, the patient experienced headache for a couple of days. Treatment for the event included ibuprofen. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of the events, headache and 16 years old received vaccine, was considered resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of product administration error  Product administered to patient of inappropriate age for mRNA-1273, lot # unknown with event of headache.Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

17 2021-03-03 fever Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes ... Read more
Close
Pt reports onset of dizziness, chest tightness, shortness of breath that started acutely 45 minutes to 1 hour after receiving her second Moderna vaccination on 2/24/21. She reported that she was told by her employer that the symptoms were due to the Moderna vaccine. She reportedly developed fever and some throat discomfort as well. Symptoms became persistent and disrupted sleep and was unable to work. She sought medical attention in the ER for persistent symptoms on 2/26/21. Extensive workup was essentially normal. She received Zofran, Decadron, IVFs, and Albuterol inhaler while in the ER. She reported improvement in her chest tightness and SOB after Albuterol. She was discharged home with instructions to f/u with her PCP in a couple of days for recheck.

17 2021-04-20 headache, malaise Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt we... Read more
Close
Severe headache; Worst migraine; Excessive vomitting; Patient under 18 given vaccine; Hasn't felt well; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of HEADACHE (Severe headache) and VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) in a 17-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 627A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). Concomitant products included DULOXETINE, CLONIDINE, HYDROXYZINE, AMITRIPTYLINE, RAMELTEON and ETHINYLESTRADIOL, NORGESTIMATE (MONO LINYAH) for an unknown indication. On 16-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 08-Mar-2021, the patient experienced MALAISE (Hasn't felt well). On 16-Mar-2021, the patient experienced PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine). On 08-Apr-2021, the patient experienced VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 11-Apr-2021, the patient experienced HEADACHE (Severe headache) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and MIGRAINE (Worst migraine). On 08-Apr-2021, VOMITING (Excessive vomitting) had resolved. At the time of the report, HEADACHE (Severe headache), MIGRAINE (Worst migraine), PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Patient under 18 given vaccine) and MALAISE (Hasn't felt well) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On an unknown date, White blood cell count: elevated (High) Elevated. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. Patient was treated with fluids, Zofran, Benadryl, Tylenol 800mg and Aspirin for headaches. Company comment: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Close
Inappropriate age at vaccine administration; Fever; Chills; bodyache; Seizure; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of SEIZURE (Seizure) in a 17-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. No Medical History information was reported. On 24-May-2021, the patient received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On an unknown date, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 24-May-2021, the patient experienced SEIZURE (Seizure) (seriousness criterion medically significant), PYREXIA (Fever), CHILLS (Chills) and MYALGIA (bodyache). On an unknown date, the patient experienced PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Inappropriate age at vaccine administration). At the time of the report, SEIZURE (Seizure), PRODUCT ADMINISTERED TO PATIENT OF INAPPROPRIATE AGE (Inappropriate age at vaccine administration), PYREXIA (Fever), CHILLS (Chills) and MYALGIA (bodyache) outcome was unknown. Not Provided No concomitant medications were provided by the reporter. No treatment information was provided. Company comment: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events Seizure, Pyrexia, Chills, and Myalgia, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. This report also refers to a case of product administered to patient of inappropriate age for mRNA-1273, lot # unknown, with no associated AEs.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events Seizure, Pyrexia, Chills, and Myalgia, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. This report also refers to a case of product administered to patient of inappropriate age for mRNA-1273, lot # unknown, with no associated AEs.

I had no pain or discomfort immediately after the shot, during the 15 minute observation period, or an hour after. About 2 hours later (at 2:00 pm), I developed some hives around my neck, and the part of my arm near the injection site started to become more and more sore. I applied Benadryl to the hives and they went away. However, my left arm hurt to touch or move, much worse than any vaccine I've had before (flu, HPV). That night, I had trouble sleeping because the discomfort because of the sore left arm. I also could not sleep because of chest tightness and pressure, which worsened when lying down, but that pressure did not progress to the point of wheezing (I have asthma). Sleeping on my back was the only option because sleeping on either side was painful, which worsened the chest pressure. When I woke up, my fingers felt stiff and I had joint pain in both hands, more so in my left hand. Throughout this, I did not see any redness on my arm. This day it was agonizing to move my left arm. I could pick things up, but raising it above my the height of my waist or twisting it behind my back to get on my backpack was near impossible and was avoided. The chest pressure went away. The second night, I still had trouble sleeping, but the pain was much better, although I still could not sleep on my side. When I woke up, I had no more joint pain. That day, although the left arm was still sore, I could move it pretty well. If I made too strong of a movement, it felt like the injection site would tense up, the pain would slowly ramp up, and then diminish. That afternoon, at 4:30, I was able to play tennis with minimal soreness, and that night, I was able to sleep on my side. The following day, I had a cough, but that might have been because I didn't dress for the weather, and experiences close to zero soreness.

I received my second dose of the COVID 19 Moderna vaccine on Tuesday morning. By Tuesday night I started to have virtually every side effect that Moderna listed including; fatigue, headache, muscle pain, joint pain, chills, nausea and vomiting, and extreme fever. The next morning as I woke up in attempt tp get ready for work, I was not feeling any better and began to feel light headed, and felt the need to vomit. As I had the feeling of needing to vomit, I turned to do so and fainted. From accounts by my family, I was told I woke up, and quickly passed out a second time. As I was awoken, there was probably a minute before I fainted for a third time. All three times I was told I lost consciousness. I was awoken and by that point my family had contacted emergency responders. Paramedics arrived and took all necessary vitals. I did not pass out after that third time. As I expected all side effects Moderna listed, I did not expect to feel as bad as I did and I thought it was worth reporting what happened to be the next day. It caused a panic and I was scared and nervous as I was unsure why that was happening. I've tried to look up articles and links between passing out and the vaccine and all I can find is people fainting as they get the vaccine (which is common for any shot) but nothing for fainting that long after the vaccine was administered. I just wanted to report my incident.

Seven hours after receiving my second dose, I developed flu-like symptoms--fever of 100-101 degrees, full body aches, fatigue, and chills, in addition to a sore left arm. These symptoms continued for 18 hours. It was difficult to sleep. I had the flu three years ago but this felt more severe. Symptoms were treated first with 200mg ibuprofen with no response and then with Tylenol, which improved symptoms. I stayed in bed for most of those 18 hours to rest. Two days after receiving my second dose, I had a headache for the whole day. The headache then became a migraine. Both treated with aspirin. Three days after the second dose, I felt fatigued, weak, and still had a headache. To my understanding, the first two days of ailment reflect my body's immune response and the final two are typical of my body's stress response. However, I have not experienced either in response to a vaccine. I should also mention my first menstrual cycle after receiving the first dose of the vaccine was shorter than usual. My periods are not always regular so it may be a coincidence, not causation.

No concomitant medication provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not applicable. 21 2021-02-04 fatigue, fever About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injecti... Read more
Close
About 3-4 hours after the injection was given, my left arm began to hurt at the sight of the injection. It was sore red and beginning to swell. After a couple more hours it was difficult to even move my arm; it felt as if my tricep was almost entirely immobilized. These symptoms persisted for about three days, with increasingly less intensity, and after the fourth day, I had no adverse symptoms. Exactly six days after receiving the vaccine, the area where the injection was given (tricep) began to feel itchy. When I tried to scratch it, the itch was not relieved but only worsened and began to swell and turn red. By the following day (7 days after injection), the site of injection and area surrounding the site of injection (about 6 inches along my upper and 3-4 inches in width) had swelled up more and was significantly more inflamed than my opposite arm which hadn't changed at all. It had a similar swelling, itch, and pain to the sensation one experiences after getting bitten by a mosquito, but in this case a very very large mosquito bite. By the evening of the seventh day, I began feeling very fatigued both mentally and physically and felt very subtle body aches that usually signal the early signs of a fever (at least for me). Upon feeling feverish symptoms I made a drink of turmeric and ginger root powder with honey and laid down for about an hour in an attempt to rest. After an hour, the body aches and fatigue lessened in intensity but my arm was still swelling and now feeling hot in temperature. The itching was unbearable. I went to go take a warm shower later that night and started to feel a mixture of pressure and pain traveling up my arm and into my chest. I began feeling my lymph nodes on the left side of my breast to find that a lymph node in my armpit and another one on the side of my breast had enlarged to about two inches in diameter. They were painful to the touch and noticeably sore when left untouched. These symptoms persisted with no change for about 2 days. After two days, the swelling and itching in my arm went away but my lymph nodes were still inflamed. They did not reduce in size or in pain until about 7 days after the first signs of these symptoms. After a week all symptoms went away.

It was weird again; Turning into a bruise; Felt crappy; A couple of bad breakthrough bleeding episodes; Menstrual cycle was interrupted; Felt off; In her right leg raised hive; Headache; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 21-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced a couple of bad breakthrough bleeding episodes, Menstrual cycle was interrupted, Felt crappy, Felt off, In her right leg raised hive, Headache, Turning into a bruise and It was weird again. The patient's medical history was reported as migraines. Concomitant medications were not reported. On 27 Feb 2021, prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 013A21A) intramuscularly in the right thigh for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 27 FEB 2021, the patient experienced Raised hive (Urticaria) about the size of a half dollar, after that she "felt off" (fall) had a headache (Headache) and Felt crappy (Malaise), and she had a couple of bad breakthrough bleeding episodes (Hemorrhage) which was assessed as medically significant, and the patient also experienced interrupted Menstrual cycle (Menstrual disorder). On 07 MAR 2021, the patient experienced Turning into a bruise (Contusion) and on 08 MAR 2021 it was weird again (Feeling abnormal). Laboratory details were not provided. Treatment medication was provided as Tylenol. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. At the time of this report, the outcome of the events Hemorrhage, Menstrual disorder, Contusion, Malaise, Feeling abnormal, Fall, Urticaria and Headache was considered as unknown.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Approximately 12 hours after the event, I had throat swelling, chills, sweats, temperature of 102.5, headache, muscle soreness, dizziness, lightheadedness. Onset was over the course of about 1 hour. I had previously taken part in the double-blinded Astrazeneca in COVID-19 trials (meaning I did not know I was vaccinated) in November 2019, so the nurse told me that the response could really be from anything: partly due to some interaction between the vaccines, allergy, and/or already producing antibodies. I was unblinded and told I was given the Astrazeneca vaccine. Interestingly, I had none of these responses to just the Astrazeneca vaccines, just a bit of soreness after the first one. I have never had such a strong response, and I believe this is the highest my temperature has ever been, and my lymph nodes are still swollen. I am much better now; however, even last night and this morning, I was feeling unwell.

21 2021-03-25 fatigue, chills I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly f... Read more
Close
I received an allergy immunotherapy shot the day before my first dose of the vaccine and instantly felt nauseous and extremely tired after receiving the vaccine, which continued for two days after receiving tut. Three days later, I woke up struggling to breathe (but not anaphylactic), covered in hives, itchy all over, shaking, disoriented, and chilled but not truly feverish. I reported this to my allergist, who prescribed prednisone and suggested the vaccine combined with immunotherapy were too much for my immune system for one week. The hives, itchiness, and difficulty breathing lasted about four days. I struggled with fatigue and nausea for over two weeks, stopping all school and work in the meantime. After my second dose, I feel just a bit tired and sore, so I think this truly was a bad reaction to the two injections combined rather than to the vaccine itself. Still, it was a debilitating experience, and I would recommend considering putting out guidance that other immunotherapy patients space out their allergy injections and vaccines farther than I did.

I developed Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (low levels of platelets) and menorrhagia due to the vaccine according to my doctor. I believe there have been about 30 cases of this occurring so far. In my case, I took the vaccine and felt relatively tired for two days. There were no other symptoms. About a week later, I got my period after not having it for a couple months. The blooding was light for a few days, but then got extremely heavy. After about a week of very heavy bleeding, I went to urgent care. They took blood tests, and found that I had a critically low level of platelets (6 platelets when the normal range is 150-400). I was admitted to the ER for multiple days, and they gave a platelet transfusion and IVIG fluids, which has helped considerably. I also had to take steroids to suppress my immune system so that my platelets could increase.

After about 5 minutes of administering the vaccine, the associate overlooking the observation area came to tell me a patient was not feeling well. I immediately grabbed my carat and went out to the IMZ area next to pharmacy. The patient was still seated and she was conscious, but appeared very weak, sweaty, and slightly pale and cold to the touch. I immediately made sure she could respond to my questions. She was able to respond. I asked if she had eaten before coming in and she confirmed she had not eaten that day yet. I checked her blood pressure and it was 68/33. I stayed by her side and her mother was fanning her on the other side. I had her take several breaths in and out and could visually see her responses improving. She asked for water, which her father handed to her. I checked her blood pressure again and it was up to 125/68. She reported feeling much better and was able to joke around with her sister who also received the vaccine at the same time. I asked her to sit for an additional 15 minutes, on top of her original 30 minutes, and told her parents I would be back to check her blood pressure gain. I came back into the pharmacy and prepared another vaccine. After I administered the next vaccine, I checked her blood pressure again, which read 95/68 and her mom stated this was normal for her. I advised her to stand up slowly before walking. A few minutes later she came to the pharmacy window for her vaccine card and reported feeling normal and her parents thanked me and they all left.

The date of the second dose was 05/25/2021, which is when the side effects started. I had the normal and expected effects, such as a sore arm and fatigue. I began my period that morning, before I went in for the shot. I would like to be as detailed as possible, so I will likely include some graphic details in this description. My apologies in advance. My period normally lasts 3-4 days and is moderate (as far as I know) regarding blood loss. After the second dose, the flow was extremely heavy and my period lasted for almost an entire week (7 days). It was miserable. I was bloated and tender in that area, and extremely tired. I was also cramping, which is unusual for me nowadays. About two weeks after that, I felt a stabbing or ripping pain in the uterus area. It stayed for about two days, throbbing every minute or so. I could not sleep those days. It was not so unbearable that I could not perform everyday actions, but it was taking up a good portion of my thoughts that weekend. After that, it went away and I thought it was over. About three days ago from today (today is June 22nd, or 06/22/2021), the pain returned and I knew it meant the start of my period. The timing was normal. The next day I began bleeding, but the flow is again much heavier than normal. The pain is back and much worse than before. I am going through many more pads than usual and it is, for me, a worrying amount of blood. Since this is the second period in a row I am experiencing this, I felt it was necessary to report it in. I hope this is okay and not taking resources from those with worse issues. I would also like to note that I experienced my first panic attack in 5 years the night of my second dose (for no reason- they've always had a concrete reason for occurring) and my anxiety was notably worse that week (I am on medication and was otherwise doing very well managing the anxiety). During the attack I experienced the usual symptoms: my throat closing up and making it harder to breathe, and uncontrollable shaking and crying. I was not thinking of anything that would make me nervous at the time of the attack. I had just finished an online gaming session with a friend and was showering to prepare for bed, so I was fully relaxed. Additionally, my mental health has notably dipped a bit over the last month, though there are a number of factors at play and I don't want to blame the vaccine for that. However, I was told to at least make note of it here just in case there does end up being a correlation.

No obvious edema of the lips or tongue. No respiratory distress. No stridor. She is 98% on room air. In IVs immediately established. She is given 125 mg of Solu-Medrol, 20 Pepcid and 50 of Benadryl. Following all of her medications, she no longer has any of her symptoms. Her rash and hives has completely resolved. I discussed this with Dr. who was in agreement that she is stable for discharge. She will be sent home on additional 3 day course of prednisone to be started tomorrow, clear 10 for 10 days and Pepcid for 10 days. Questions addressed and answered prior to discharge. Patient discharged home in stable condition.

22 2021-02-16 fever, chills Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels ... Read more
Close
Aggravated very quickly; Everything went blank; She can't talk and when she tries to talk she feels like she has the hiccups where she can barely get the words to talk; when she has a hiccup her whole chest hurts; Hiccup; Numbness; Her whole right side would jerk uncontrollably; Weak; fever; itching; sore arm / burning; chills; A spontaneous report (United States) was received from a consumer who was also a 22-year-old female patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine who experienced sore arm/ burning (injection site pain), fever (pyrexia), chills, itching (injection site pruritus), numbness (injection site numbness), weak (asthenia), whole right side would jerk uncontrollably (myoclonus), everything went blank (loss of consciousness), couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups (aphasia), her whole chest hurt (chest discomfort), and quickly became aggravated (anger). The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient received her first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly in her right deltoid for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 06 Jan 2021, the patient experienced a sore arm, fever, chills, itching and burning. On 07 Jan 2021, on the site where the patient received the injection, she felt numbness and weak. Her whole right-side body would jerk uncontrollably. The patient went to two emergency rooms where they stated they did not know what was wrong and gave her a steroid injection that temporarily helped calm her down. On 08 Jan 2021, the patient stared at the door and everything went blank. She could not talk and when she tried to talk, she felt like she had the hiccups. She experienced her whole chest hurting when she had a hiccup. On 25 Jan 2021 and 26 Jan 2021, the patient saw two neurologists, who did testing. The patient's jerking was random, there were no triggers for it, and she did not know how to control or stop it. These adverse reactions made the patient become aggravated very quickly, which was not like her. On an unknown date, the patient stated it was the first day in the past month she had been able to talk all day. Treatment for the events included a steroid shot. Action taken with the second dose of mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome for the events, sore arm/ burning, fever, chills, itching, numbness, weak, whole right side would jerk uncontrollably, everything went blank, couldn't talk and when she tried to talk she felt like she had the hiccups and her whole chest hurt, and quickly became aggravated, was not reported.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information which indicates a strong temporal association between the use of the product and the onset of the reported events a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Chills, fever, injection site pruritus and injection site pain are consistent with the known safety profile of mRNA-1273.

I received diphenhydrAMINE (BENADRYL) injection 50 mg, famotidine (PF) (PEPCID) injection 20 mg, methylPREDNISolone sodium succinate (PF) (SOLU-MEDROL) injection 125 mg, sodium chloride 0.9 % iv bolus, and acetaminophen (TYLENOL) tablet 650 mg. I was discharged after 10:00 PM and sent home with a prescription for predniSONE 20 mg and famotidine 20 mg. My facial swelling and hives have gone down but neither have completely resolved since being discharged. I am also experiencing full body aches and fatigue at this time (3 PM on Saturday, January 30).

Other than these symptoms, I have also experienced muscle aches, chills, and a very sore arm. I understand that nausea/vomiting is a reported side effect with Moderna for some people, but considering I've never experienced this symptom in any other vaccine (and never vomited back to back so quickly in a short period of time) I figured I would report my symptoms.

Once I was able to remove the mask and breathe deeply, the reaction subsided after two minutes. The pharmacist, after my reaction began to subside, stated that they had an epipen ready to administer if needed. I was never administered the epipen. The pharmacist asked me to wait 30 minutes instead of the general 15 minutes before leaving the site. Because the symptoms went away and did not return within the 30 minutes, I left the site. After the vaccination, I experienced a low-grade fever for 79 hours, chills, a headache, muscle aches, and extreme fatigue. After realizing my reaction was not considered ?normal,? I began to research and realized these symptoms align with anaphylaxis, even though they subsided quickly after experiencing them.

Diphenhydramine administered and per patient a medic was called who reported 5-6 minutes of seizure-like activity and patient being non-responsive with blood pressure 80/palp en route to the emergency department (ED). In the ED patient received epinephrine, steroids, and diphenhydramine, monitored for several housrs, and discharged. Two days later patient reports waking up and feeling as if throat was closing up again, self-administered Epi-Pen and diphenhydramine, and returned to the ED. Steroids and diphenhydramine were adminsitered, patient was monitored, symptoms resolved, and patient was discharged. Since vaccination patient reports fatigue, dizziness, lightheadedness, persistent diarrhea, and numbness. Patient advised to continue home management and follow-up allergy testing recommended.

Central Venous Sinus Thrombosis in Superior Sagittal Sinus I arrived home at 12:38 on Sunday, 5/9, and opened the door to see my sister with facial droop, slurred speech and a contracted right hand/fingers. She was crying and immediately knew she was having a stroke. She had been trying to clasp some jewelry while getting ready for Mother's Day. She was able to walk down to the car with me no problem (no extremity involvement other than right hand/fingers). We arrived at the hospital within 10 minutes and she was a Code Stroke. A CT scan showed the clots as well as a tiny Subarachnoid bleed and she was admitted to NeuroICU. The symptoms waxed and waned for a few hours and at one point she developed the droop again, had headache and heartburn and vomited. A CT scan was repeated after some Heparin had entered her system and it was stable/not worse; subarach bleed was not changed and Heparin was continued. She has now been admitted for 3 days and the Heparin is complete. She is now being transitioned to oral Xaralto. She has no deficits whatsoever and has made a full recovery so far. We are still pending the results of her coagulation studies to see if she has a hereditary condition. The doctors believe the clot is due to her Nuvaring Estrogen, which is most likely. However, I would still like to report this event just in case.

On the morning of 1/8/2021 (exactly 6 days after the first dose of the Moderna vaccine), I woke up with large hives concentrated mostly on my upper body (face, neck, chest, stomach). I tried taking various antihistamines (excluding Benadryl, which would later prove effective) to combat the hives, but they were largely ineffective. The hives shifted throughout the day, starting in my upper body and working their way down to my lower extremities. The next day, exactly one week after receiving the vaccine, I woke up with worse hives (now all over my body, mostly concentrated on my stomach, hips, and legs) and angioedema in my face. At this point, I went to the hospital and received a course of IV fluids/steroids/Benadryl/anti-nausea medication and all symptoms subsisted. Symptoms returned a few hours after discharge, where I continued an oral regimen of the aforementioned medications. The next day, 8 days after the initial dose, my symptoms were equally severe and coupled with gastrointestinal distress, feverishness (likely due to dehydration from the Benadryl) and nausea. This morning (1/11/2021), 9 days after receiving the vaccine, my hives have largely subsisted. In summation, starting 6 days after receiving my first dose of the Moderna vaccine, I experienced 3 full days and nights of severe hives and swelling.

Passed out twice; Pain in the injection site; Slight headache; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 24-year-old, female patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache. The patient's medical history was not reported. No concomitant medications were reported. On 26 Dec 2020 at 1:58 pm, approximately three hours prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: 026L2DA) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 26 Dec 2020, at 5:00 pm, the patient passed out. She also had pain in the injection site and a slight headache. On 27 Dec 2020, at 8:30 am, the patient passed out again. No treatment information was provided. The Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome for the events, passed out twice, pain in the injection site, and slight headache was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 24 year old female patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of loss of consciousness and non-serious expected event of injection site pain and headache. The event occurred apparently few hours after first dose of mRNA-1273 (Lot # 026L2DA) administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Patient reported: A fast heartbeat; Dizziness and weakness; Fever CHIEF COMPLAINT: FEVER (pt received second dose of covid vaccine on 1/20 at 1800, fever and chest tightness, history cardiomyopathy); presented to ED following day at 04:30 AM. Briefly this is a 24-year-old with hypertrophic cardiomyopathy myopathy without obstruction presenting with fevers, chest tightness, and rigors after her 2nd COVID vaccine yesterday. She took Tylenol at home yesterday and on presentation this morning she already felt better. Her chest tightness was no longer present on admission and did not recur. EKG relatively unchanged from prior studies. She was febrile with an initial temperature of 39.3° C and tachycardic to 110. She was given 1 g of Tylenol and 15 mg Toradol as well as 2 L normal saline. Her temperature came down to 37.1 and her heart rate came down to 90. Subjectively she felt a lot better and was comfortably sitting upright in her bed. Her blood pressure on admission was 105/58 and had dropped to 91/45, she was given an additional 1 L of normal saline (for a total of 3L) and her blood pressure improved to 103/46. She was able to ambulate without dizziness. She was discharged home with instructions to return if she significantly worsened, developed shortness of breath or experience recurrence of her chest tightness.

Close
On January 21 I received my first dose of Moderna vaccine on my left arm. After the vaccine I had a red lump that was hot and a bruise that only lasted 2 days. Everything was fine until the January 28th when I developed a large red lump during the day while at work that was severely itchy and hot. When I got home from work I had a low grade fever. I made an appointment with my primary care for the next day which was Friday the 29th. My doctor told me she believes I had cellulitis. I was given an antibiotic 2x a day for 7 days. She drew a purple circle around the area and told me that if it goes outside the marked area or I feel any new symptoms, to go to the emergency room. Saturday morning on the 30th i woke up to my entire arm red and hot. I felt like I had a huge sunburn. I couldn?t put my sweatshirt on because it was so hot. The emergency room doctor told me I was fine and to keep taking the antibiotics that were given to me yesterday from my primary care doctor. After the emergency room I went to work and started to feel dizzy and nauseous. My hands became sweaty but the rest of my body was cold. I started having a butterfly feeling in my chest. My Apple Watch alerted me that my heart rate was over 100 bpm. That night before bed I had another low grade fever. On Sunday the 31st I noticed the red area was gone but instead it was a dark purple. I felt okay Sunday besides a rapid pulse. Monday February 1st I woke up out of a dead sleep sweating, butterfly feeling in my chest and dizzy. I tried to take my pulse while laying down but it was so fast I couldn?t keep up with it. I put my Apple Watch on which alerted me immediately that my pulse was 152 bpm. I slowly got up but then I passed out falling off of my bed. I couldn?t get any words out because my heart was beating so fast that I couldn?t breathe. I was sweating horribly and had a hard time walking. Had absolutely no strength in my left hand, my arm was purple/red, cold and numb. My arm felt like someone punched me repeatedly and gave me a dead arm. I called my primary doctors office and they were able to get me in that afternoon. All morning my pulse was spiking and then drastically dropping. About an hour and a half before I went to the doctor everything was fine. I was able to talk but still struggled with breathing while talking. The doctor ordered an EKG which came back clear. My pulse and blood pressure was also fine. The doctor told me she believed all of the symptoms I had were from the medication I take at night (doxazosin-to relax my muscles and help with sleep.) She also told me she believed some of it was my mental health issues taking over. She told me the cellulitis looked fine and sent me home. Later that day I felt exhausted and when I woke up from a nap, I had a fever of 100.5. Took Tylenol and it dropped to 99.5 but wouldn?t go any lower. February 2nd I woke up to a large red ring outside of the purple marker, numb finger tips and butterfly feeling in my chest. All day I received alerts that my pulse was falling and spiking. I sent my primary doctor an email and she told me she didn?t think it was cellulitis anymore, maybe a hematoma but she wasn?t sure. Since January 28th I still struggle everyday with the butterfly feeling in my chest, blurry vision, low grade temps, alerts of pulse, dizziness and breathing difficulties. My arm is always hot, my finger tips are numb and sometimes the strength in my hand is gone. The top of my arm is always a dark purple with red blotches and other times my entire arm is red and hot. When my pulse is very fast, I have a hard time talking, remembering what I was going to say and focusing. I?ve had multiple coworkers ask me if I?m okay because I?ll randomly stop talking and stare off and then I?m alerted that my pulse has either spiked or dropped drastically after spiking. My pulse is never consistent. It is always ranging from 57-155bpm. I realized at first I may have what they call ?COVID arm? but my symptoms haven?t gotten any better. No answers have been given to me or a diagnosis. The first diagnosis that they thought was cellulitis. Then it was ?in my head and behavioral.? Then it was a hematoma. Now it?s an ?I don?t know.? I have tried Benadryl for the itching, ice packs for the days that I?m swollen, Tylenol for the fevers and pain but I never have any relief.

Vasovagal syncope (loss of consciousness) Tonic seizure (tensing and twitching of arms) Irregular heartbeat (per EKG) Extremely low blood pressure I received the vaccine at a public health pop-up, drive through clinic for first responders - I accessed the vaccine through my employer as a first responder. The vaccine was administered to my left arm without complication at approximately 1:00pm (my scheduled appointment). I proceeded to the area designated for patients to be observed after receiving the vaccine and was asked to wait 15 minutes. I recall getting to the observation area then telling my spouse I felt unwell - after the event he notified me that I told him I was about to pass out and asked him to get medical help. I lost consciousness approximately 5-10 minutes following the vaccine. My husband reported that after losing consciousness I seemed to have a minor seizure, as evidenced by my head jerking and my arms and fingers "tensing and curling up". I was sitting in the passenger seat of my car at this time, so I suffered no fall or fall related injury. Public health officials and EMT responded. They indicated to my spouse that I had experienced a vasovagal syncope episode and that I had "gone tonic"/ had a "tonic seizure". They took my blood pressure, which was very low (I don't recall exactly but it was 80 over something). They also took my blood sugar among other things that I do not recall. I was given oxygen and put into an ambulance. I was shaking, so they wrapped me in blankets. I believe they may have done an EKG and placed a blood pressure cuff while I was in the ambulance, but I do not recall any specifics about this. The EMT also drew my blood, placed an IV, and administered IV fluids while I was in the ambulance. I was taken by ambulance to the emergency department

Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The event, very nauseous, was considered resolved on 08 Jan 2021. Rapid heartbeat; Shortness of breath; Pain at injection site; Chills; Fatigue; Fever; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 25 years-old, female patient who experienced rapid heartbeat/MedDRA PT: tachycardia, shortness of breath/MedDRA PT: dyspnoea, pain at injection site/MedDRA PT: vaccination site pain, chills/MedDRA PT: chills, fatigue/MedDRA PT: fatigue, and fever/MedDRA PT: pyrexia. The patient's medical history included anemia and low immune system. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 23 Jan 2021, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot # 025A202A) intramuscularly (injection site not provided) for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 23 Jan 2021, after receiving vaccination, the patient experienced pain at injection site, chills, fever, fatigue and shortness of breath. On 24 Jan 2021, the patient experienced rapid heartbeat. The patient was hospitalized and during hospitalization, heart rate was noted as 125 bpm which reduced down to 110 bpm. The patient was discharged on 25 Jan 2021. Following hospitalization, patient had ongoing fever and was advised to contact hospital for direction regarding readmission. Treatment included self-administered Tylenol, six times daily. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was unknown. The events chills and shortness of breath were considered resolved on 24 Jan 2021. The events pain at injection site, fatigue, and rapid heartbeat were considered resolved on an unknown date. The event fever was considered not resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 25-year-old female who experienced serious expected events of tachycardia and dyspnea along with nonserious expected events of fever, chills, fatigue and vaccination site pain. The events occurred 1 day after the first dose of mRNA-1273. Treatment included Tylenol. Based on current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

Feelt very tired; loss of consciousness with fainting; Felt like her throat was closing; Chills; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 25-years-old patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced loss of consciousness, felt like her throat was closing, chills and felt very tired The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. Laboratory data was Prolong QT interval on ECG reported. On 20 Jan 2021, approximately same day prior to the onset of the events, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Lot number: unknown) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 20 Jan 2021, 5 minutes after vaccination, the patient felt like her throat was closing, chills, lightheaded and fainted. In the ER the work up for syncope revealed prolonged qt interval on ECG. Treatment included Benadryl, Magnesium, fluids. The patient was discharged on the same day but she still feels tired having brain fog. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not reported. The outcome of events were not reported; Reporter's Comments: Very limited information regarding this event/s has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

Heart rate continues to be anywhere from 85-135 bpm while I am at rest. Palpitations have also continued and are worse at night. Shortness of breath has also continued, but is not as bad as before.

The patient's medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included spironolactone 50mg. On 11-Feb-2021, the patient received her second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (batch: 030M20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. The patient said she only had 0.3ML instead of 0.5ML. The patient also reported that she had a bad headache and chills the same day after being vaccinated but went well after taking Tyenol. Patient also reported that she had a sore arm. Treatment for the event included paracetamol. The outcome of event, sore arm, was unknown. The outcome of the events, headache, chills, and only had 0.3ML instead of 0.5ML of vaccine, was considered resolved.; Reporter's Comments: This report refers to a case of incorrect dose administered for mRNA-1273 (lot # 030M20A) with associated AEs reported as headache, chills and sore arm

25 2021-03-15 fatigue, respiratory tract congestion, fever, headache, sinus congestion, throat pain, chills Around 6:00 pm on the day of vaccination I started to feel very fatigued and developed body aches - ... Read more
Close
Around 6:00 pm on the day of vaccination I started to feel very fatigued and developed body aches - this felt similar to the beginning of developing Covid-19 symptoms. (I had Covid-19 back in November of 2020) Around 8:00 pm I had developed some head congestion and swollen lymph nodes along with some throat pain and sinus congestion - again feeling very similar to Covid-19 symptoms. Around 10:00 pm as I was heading to bed the symptoms became a lot worse, I had pretty intense body aches and started to experience chills as well as a slight fever (around 99.5 in F). At this time the symptoms felt similar to how I had felt during the worst of my previous Covid-19 symptoms, very weak and achy, headache was very bad, and felt very uncomfortable overall. Around 2:00 am on March 13 I woke up with a fever of 101.8. The previous symptoms had also gotten worse, I was having a hard time getting out of bed because things were very uncomfortable, I drank a lot of water and took some ibuprofen to combat the fever, about an hour after this the fever had come down to about 99.9 and I was able to fall asleep, but before taking the medication I couldn't have fallen asleep because of the discomfort of the aches, chills, and fever. Throughout the following day I was unable to complete many of my day to day activities without taking a daytime cold and flu medication. With the medication I still felt sick but was able to walk around and complete some simple household chores, this carried through into the evening, when the medication wore off the chills and aches and headache were much worse and I still had a fever around 99-100. That night I was able to sleep with the cold and flu medication taken right before bed. Upon waking up the next morning (March 14) I still had some congestion, headache, and general discomfort but the worst of the aches were gone and I no longer had a fever, these symptoms continued to diminish throughout the day. On March 15 and March 16th I have had a slight lingering congestion headache, this also feels really similar to the lingering headache I had upon recovering from Covid-19. It is not debilitating and is continuing to improve. Otherwise I am feeling healthy again and have been able to complete my usual activities and even exercise. Overall the symptoms felt like a couple days of having Covid-19 again, but recovery was much faster, and it was definitely worth receiving that first dose of the vaccine and getting started with the process of doing my part to reduce community spread.

One week after vaccine, injection site became extremely swollen (approx. 2"x3" induration), burning hot to the touch, tender & itchy, arm became numb. General malaise, low grade fever. Site reaction spread down arm, went to urgent care & was told it may be cellulitis & was given antibiotics & told to go to ER if it continued to spread. It spread outside of line that was drawn the next day so I went to ER. They did nothing & told me remain on antibiotics & to see allergist & PCP. Reaction continued to spread, arm/hand numbness & general feeling of illness, slight fever continued for approx. 2 weeks following vaccine. Site reaction fully subsided visually by 1/26 (began 1/15). Allergist suggested it was severe immune reaction to vaccine. Felt generally unwell for approx. 5 weeks following vaccine. Was told I should not get second dose or any covid/flu vaccines in the future. I have history of poor reaction to vaccines/site reactions.

I felt like a different person. The pain was gone. The only lingering effect was when I would get up from sitting down, I would be dizzy and my head would throb for a few seconds. Client received her Moderna Covid vaccine dose 2 lot #: 027C21A and expires 7/1/21 at approximately 1:05pm. PHN noticed client had mask down and asked client to cover her nose, since she was waiting for her mother to get medical consult. Client then reports she "just feels really hot." PHN observes client is alert and oriented x4 and reports no dizziness, no shortness of breath, no blurred vision, and no chest pain. At 1:15pm, vitals are: blood pressure: 160/100, heart rate:81 and unable to get oxygen saturation due to long acrylic nails. Client reports not taking any medications, no known allergies and only has history of rosacea. PHN alert Lead PHN to come assist with client who is having a reaction. PHN assesses client and observes flushed face and rash on upper back and front neck area. Client reports to that she feels "lightheaded", PHN asks RN to get gravity chair and switch client to gravity chair. Client able to transfer herself to anti-gravity chair by herself. PHN offered client Benadryl and client accepted. Client reports she can get family to pick her up. At 1:18pm, PHN provides client with oral Benadryl 50 mg. Vitals are heart rate: 81 and blood pressure: 170/100. Client reports she feels "hot", her head "feels weird" and she feels like her "heart is racing." RN assists by fanning client. RN takes over vitals blood pressure: 180/130 at 1:20pm and client reports feeling hot everywhere. While PHN is assessing client PHN activates 911 at 1:23pm. At 1:25pm, client reports she feels "throbbing in her head and chest", "heavy breathing", "lightheaded" and PHN notes flushed face. Vitals are: Blood pressure:180/120 heart rate:86 and oxygen: 98%. Fire department arrives at 1:29pm and assumes care. At 1:34pm client was wheeled out of facility on gurney and was taken to hospital.

25 2021-06-18 fever, dehydration liver damage due to dehydration; nausea; vomiting; dehydrated; could not go to work because of illne... Read more
Close
liver damage due to dehydration; nausea; vomiting; dehydrated; could not go to work because of illness; could not eat or drink and hold anything down; feverish; lost lot of hair; This spontaneous case was reported by a patient (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of LIVER INJURY (liver damage due to dehydration), NAUSEA (nausea), VOMITING (vomiting) and DEHYDRATION (dehydrated) in a 25-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch nos. 008C21A and 030B21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. Concurrent medical conditions included Anxiety. Concomitant products included CLONAZEPAM for Anxiety, AMFETAMINE ASPARTATE, AMFETAMINE SULFATE, DEXAMFETAMINE SACCHARATE, DEXAMFETAMINE SULFATE (ADDERALL) for an unknown indication. On 07-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 05-May-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 2 dosage form. On 06-May-2021, the patient experienced NAUSEA (nausea) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), VOMITING (vomiting) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), DEHYDRATION (dehydrated) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), DYSPHAGIA (could not eat or drink and hold anything down) and PYREXIA (feverish). On 07-May-2021, the patient experienced LIVER INJURY (liver damage due to dehydration) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant). In May 2021, the patient experienced ALOPECIA (lost lot of hair). On an unknown date, the patient experienced IMPAIRED WORK ABILITY (could not go to work because of illness). The patient was hospitalized until 12-May-2021 due to DEHYDRATION, LIVER INJURY, NAUSEA and VOMITING. On 09-May-2021, NAUSEA (nausea), VOMITING (vomiting) and DYSPHAGIA (could not eat or drink and hold anything down) had resolved. On 12-May-2021, DEHYDRATION (dehydrated) had resolved. At the time of the report, LIVER INJURY (liver damage due to dehydration) had resolved and ALOPECIA (lost lot of hair), IMPAIRED WORK ABILITY (could not go to work because of illness) and PYREXIA (feverish) outcome was unknown. DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 06-May-2021, Blood pressure measurement: unknown (Low) blood pressure dropped. On 07-May-2021, Liver function test: unknown (High) Elevated liver enzymes. Patient was also reported to be taking birth control pills as concomitant medications. Patient reported that several tests were done in the hospital. Patient was reported to stay in the ICU on 07-MAY-2021. Patient was treated with iv fluids, iv potassium and anti-nausea medication. Patient was reported to specifically ask if she can get some refund for the money spent for treatment at the hospital and wanted to talk to somebody from Moderna safety team and was expecting call from safety team to clarify if any refund policy for the injury and answer her questions. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
